diagram.documentation: This table provides a hierarchical breakdown of the space manufacturing system's functions, from the top-level L0 functions down to the supporting L1, L2, and L3 subfunctions. The eight L0 functions represent the primary operational capabilities of the system: (1) Conduct Autonomous Orbital Manufacturing Operations, (2) Maintain Operational Availability of Orbital Platform, (3) Ensure Compliance with Regulatory and Safety Standards, (4) Manage Resources and Logistics for Orbital Manufacturing, (5) Fault Recovery and Remote Override, (6) Monitor and Analyze System Performance, (7) On-Orbit Assembly, Activation, and Upgrade, and (8) Manage Orbital Position and Attitude. Each L0 function is further decomposed into L1, L2, and L3 subfunctions, providing increasing levels of detail on specific tasks and processes. The table also lists the inputs and outputs for each function, illustrating the flow of data, materials, and control signals through the system. This hierarchical structure allows for a comprehensive understanding of the system's functionality, from high-level operations down to detailed tasks, and facilitates traceability between system requirements and specific functional elements.
